In this statement, the President expresses his sadness over the passing of Professor Wangari Maathai. He offers his condolences to her family and the people of Kenya. The President praises Maathai's work with the Greenbelt Movement, which focused on grassroots organizing and the planting of trees. He highlights her achievements, including winning the Nobel Peace Prize, and her commitment to conservation, democracy, women's empowerment, poverty eradication, and civic engagement. The President also mentions her service in the Kenyan government, the African Union, and the United Nations. He concludes by saying that Maathai's legacy will serve as an inspiration for all to continue working towards progress.